caption.p:
Representative experiment showing inhibition of 
   Stagonosporopsis cucurbitacearum mycelial growth by the seven essential oils: 
   C.cit, 
   Cymbopogon citratus; 
   L.dent, 
   Lavandula dentata; 
   L.hyb, 
   Lavandula hybrida; 
   M.alt, 
   Melaleuca alternifolia; 
   L.nob, 
   Laurus nobilis; 
   O.maj1/2, 
   Origanum majorana 1/2, at increasing concentrations (right to left; as indicated) from 0 mg/mL (control) to 1 mg /mL, and by the fungicide combination of 25 g/L difenoconazole plus 25 g/L fludioxonil (positive control) at 0.1, 0.5 and 1 mg/mL, after 7 days of incubation at 22 ± 2 °C.
